  <mainDescription>This task involves an early assessment of the customer's business goals and job/task performance needs in order to identify&#xD;
the training and user support strategies that can best satisfy customer requirements. Technology-based strategies, such as&#xD;
Web-Based Training (WBT) or context-sensitive Electronic Performance Support Solutions (EPSS), are among the many&#xD;
strategies considered in the assessment. This task also involves developing a high level plan for the recommended approach&#xD;
that outlines the process, major tasks, schedule, skill levels, and estimated resources required to implement the training&#xD;
and user support strategies identified.</mainDescription>
  <externalId xsi:nil="true"/>
  <keyConsiderations xsi:nil="true"/>
  <purpose>The main purpose of this task is&amp;nbsp;to understand enough about the business environment and end-user job/task performance&#xD;
goals such that recommendations on the most appropriate training and user support strategies can be made to the customer.&#xD;
This task is also used for estimating and planning the development and implementation of the identified strategies.</purpose>
  <alternatives xsi:nil="true"/>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
